    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Class to manage loading frames of an animated image in small chunks. Lazy initializes only when data is actually needed. Note, once the Animated Image has loaded, the undecoded data will reside in memory until this object is released. (This is to speed up frame loads, which would otherwise have to re-acquire the data from disk) </para>
    </detaileddescription>
